  "intent_precise": "Zymo Quick-DNA/RNA Viral Kit: Using magplate (deep_well_plate, slot 3), flatplate (pcr_plate, slot 3), Liquid Waste (reservoir, slot 11), Opentrons 24 TubeRack (tuberack, slot 8). With mag_gen module. (1) Transfer from source to destination. (2) Transfer from source (multiple wells) to destination (multiple wells). (3) Transfer from source to destination. (4) Transfer 4\u00b5L from source to destination. (5) Transfer 160\u00b5L from source to destination. (6) Transfer 160\u00b5L from source to destination. (7) Engage magnets at magheightmm height for bead separation. (8) Incubate for 5 minutes. (9) Transfer 180\u00b5L from source to destination. (10) Transfer from source to destination. (11) Disengage magnets to release beads. (12) Transfer 165\u00b5L from source to destination. (13) Transfer 165\u00b5L from source to destination. (14) Engage magnets at magheightmm height for bead separation. (15) Incubate for 3 minutes. (16) Disengage magnets to release beads. (17) Incubate for 2 minutes. (18) Transfer 180\u00b5L from source A1 to destination A1. (19) Incubate for 10 minutes. (20) Disengage magnets to release beads. (21) Transfer 60\u00b5L from source to destination. (22) Transfer 50\u00b5L from source to destination. (23) Incubate for 10 minutes. (24) Engage magnets at magheightmm height for bead separation. (25) Incubate for 2 minutes. (26) Transfer 60\u00b5L from source to destination. (27) Disengage magnets to release beads.",
  "intent_concise": "Perform magnetic bead separation. (volumes 4\u00b5L-200\u00b5L, ~35 min total)",
  "intent": "For this Zymo Quick-DNA/RNA Viral Kit protocol, you'll be working with the deep well plate in slot 3 as your main magplate, a PCR plate also in slot 3, liquid waste reservoir in slot 11, and the tube rack in slot 8. Start by transferring your samples and reagents as specified, then add 4\u00b5L followed by 160\u00b5L transfers before engaging the magnets for a 5-minute incubation and transferring 180\u00b5L to waste. Continue with the wash steps using 165\u00b5L transfers, engaging magnets for 3 minutes, then perform the binding step with 180\u00b5L from A1 to A1 followed by a 10-minute incubation. Finish with the elution using 60\u00b5L and 50\u00b5L transfers, incubating for 10 minutes, then engage magnets for 2 minutes before the final 60\u00b5L transfer and magnet disengagement.",
